public vs private - IPv4 - almost running out of it
IPV6- random
Elastic IP- static IP allocation for instance or network. seperate from instance and will not be changed ,while pulbic ip for instance gets changed whenever instance is restarted.

Placement Group- you can control instance placement stratergy using placement groups.
Cluster- int low latency group in a single availability zone
Spread- across underlying hardware -critical applications(max 7 instances)
partitions- spread instances across many different partitions.
